definitions.definition: An explosion or sudden report made by the near- instantaneous decomposition or combustion of unstable substances. Specifically, combustion that spreads supersonically via shock compression .

subdefinitions.definition: Any sudden explosion made by an exothermic process (whether chemical or not) that produces a supersonic shock wave .

definitions.definition: Engine knocking , a type of improper combustion in gasoline piston engines.
